  "text": "c Using self report measures, a wide range of Gulf specific exposures have been found to be associated with ill health c There is insufficient objective evidence for any one exposure c Long term effects of low doses of postulated toxins, such as chemical agents, depleted uranium, and pesticides are uncertain but are unlikely to play an important aetiological role in the development of symptoms Education Similar syndromes have also been identified in the civilian population. A number of multi symptom, medically unexplained syndromes are very similar to those found in Gulf veterans. These conditions are chronic fatigue syndrome, total allergy syndrome, dental amalgam disease, chronic Lyme disease, sick building syndrome, multiple chemical sensitivity, fibromyalgia, and irritable bowel syndrome. These symptoms and conditions tend to overlap with each other [CITATION_1] and are commonly associated with mood. They tend to be similar in that no physical cause can be identified and stressful events are associated with their onset. They tend to diVer in the aetiological attribution of the condition given by the patient and the media, from viruses to chemicals to buildings, in the context of inadequate epidemiological or biological evidence for a causal relationship. Elevated rates of chronic fatigue syndrome and multiple chemical sensitivity have been reported in Gulf veterans.",
